\[ \text{Crude Rate} = \frac{\text{New Cancer Cases}}{\text{At Risk Population}} * 100,000 \]

Analysis

General upward trend over time among all zones on chart. Possible explanations for this could be: - increasing size of older population - better diagnosis of cancer leading to higher numbers of incidences (useful to compare to successful treatment rates / life expectancy of cancer patients to see if these also increase during the time frame) - as cancer is more prevalent in older age groups, changes in population demographics (such as younger people moving to more urban areas) could also result in higher rates but similar incidence numbers
